Lansing — Four days ahead of Michigan's filing deadline for candidates, Gov.
Gretchen Whitmer speaks at a press conference to update the public on the spread of COVID-19 on Monday, March 30, 2020.
(Photo: Governor's office photo)"We know that these deadlines are critical in terms of keeping our elections on schedule," Whitmer said when asked about the issue during a press conference.
In response to Whitmer's statement, Secretary of State Jocelyn Benson tweeted that she fully supports the "decision not to extend Michigan’s candidate filing deadline."
I fully support @GovWhitmer’s decision not to extend Michigan’s candidate filing deadline.